    <Fragment slot="subtitle"  >
     <span class="text-gray-700 text-left"> NUMSA, the official representative body of medical students at Nile University of Nigeria, transcends tribal,
      religious, linguistic, and national boundaries. Bearing the full name "NILE UNIVERSITY MEDICAL STUDENTS’
      ASSOCIATION" (NUMSA), its primary mission is to enhance the overall well-being and development of its student
      body. This encompasses academic growth and the acquisition of skills essential for thriving in the 21st century.
      NUMSA serves as a foundational stepping stone towards realizing the inherent greatness within both current and
      future students. </span> <br /> <br/> 
      <span class="text-gray-700 text-left">The association serves to represent all medical students and our interests guided
      by the rules of morality and discipline set by our prestigious college in order to enable medical students translate
      our noble initiatives to reality. </span> <br /> <br />

      <span class="text-gray-700 text-left">Comprising more than 600 medical students from diverse backgrounds, NUMSA
      stands as one of Nigeria's premier medical colleges, ranked among the top 45 institutions of its kind across the nation
      and the Federal Capital Territory. The organization boasts a well-structured framework, featuring over 28 dedicated
      service offices, all committed to catering to the needs of medical students at Nile University. </span> <br/> <br /> 
      
      <span class="text-gray-700 text-left">The driving
      force behind NUMSA is its fervent commitment to empowering the next generation of healthcare professionals. Through
      the provision of knowledge, skills, and resources, the organization fosters collaboration, advances medical education,
      extends humanitarian aid, and strives to improve healthcare access for all, thereby leaving a lasting positive impact
      on global well being.</span> <br/> <br />
      
      <span class="text-gray-700 text-left">NUMSA is affiliated with organizations, such as: Nigerian Medical Association (NMA), Nigerian
      Medical Students’ Association (NiMSA), International Federation of Medical Students’ Association (IFMSA), Federation
      of African Medical Students’ Association (FAMSA),… and other Students’ Organizations. </span>
    </Fragment>
